        <h2>
      <a href="/?q=node/24720">Victoria League (Durban Branch) papers</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="Victoria League (Durban Branch) papers" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-field-ms-title field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Title:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Victoria League (Durban Branch) papers</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-records field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Date:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">1911?-1985</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-extent field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Extent:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">17 files</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-physical-description field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Physical description:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">manuscripts, typescripts, newscuttings, photographs</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-historical-note field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Historical note:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>The Victoria League for Commonwealth Friendship was established in Britain in 1901 with the purpose of fostering closer ties between the different parts of the British Empire. The Durban Branch was founded in 1923 and was involved in various endeavours, its most memorable work being carried out during World War II</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-digitised field-type-list-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS File list:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Available at KCAL</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-scope-and-content field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Scope and Content:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>The collection comprises of 17 files. Files 1-10 consist largely of bound volumes of minutes, particularly of Executive Committee meetings, and Files 11 and 12 are bound scrapbooks of newscuttings, with File 12 including newscuttings of work done by the Victoria League in Durban during World War II. Files 13 to 16 consist primarily of correspondence and miscellaneous items, with File 14 containing correspondence written by servicemen to the Victoria League, Durban Branch. File 17 contains photographs from c1920 to 1961.  See also the collection of the <a href="/?q=node/22161">Victoria League, Pietermaritzburg Branch</a></p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-shelf field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Shelf:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">VIC</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-provenance field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Provenance:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Donation</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-local-system-number field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Local system number:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">KCAL349968</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-taxonomy-vocabulary-6 field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-above clearfix"><h3 class="field-label">Manuscript Inventory: </h3><ul class="links"><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-0"><a href="/?q=taxonomy/term/508" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">Victoria League, Durban Branch /Records</a></li></ul></div>  </div>

