        <h2>
      <a href="/?q=node/24448">Philip Townshend papers</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="Philip Townshend papers" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-field-ms-title field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Title:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Philip Townshend papers</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-records field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Date:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">189-?-19--?</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-extent field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Extent:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">22 files</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-physical-description field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Physical description:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">manuscripts, typescripts, printed material, newspaper cuttings</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-historical-note field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Historical note:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>Philip Townshend (1866-1951) was a newspaper editor and journalist. He also wrote under the pseudonyms 'Tangley Lane' and 'Flagstaff'</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-digitised field-type-list-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS File list:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Available at KCAL</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-scope-and-content field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Scope and Content:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>The collection comprises: Diaries written by Philip Townshend and his mother, Mary McKenzie Townshend during the South African War ; personal correspondence and miscellaneous material ; articles, short stories and poems written by Philip Townshend ; newscuttings</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-shelf field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Shelf:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">TOW</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-provenance field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Provenance:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">-</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-local-system-number field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Local system number:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">KCAL351657</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-taxonomy-vocabulary-6 field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-above clearfix"><h3 class="field-label">Manuscript Inventory: </h3><ul class="links"><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-0"><a href="/?q=taxonomy/term/503" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">Townshend, Philip /Papers</a></li></ul></div>  </div>

