<div id="node-24446" class="node node-content-manuscript-metadata node-promoted node-sticky node-teaser clearfix" about="/?q=node/24446" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">

        <h2>
      <a href="/?q=node/24446">John (Jock) Sutherland papers</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="John (Jock) Sutherland papers" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-field-ms-title field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Title:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">John (Jock) Sutherland papers</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-records field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Date:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">1894-1937</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-extent field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Extent:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">1 file</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-physical-description field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Physical description:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">manuscripts, printed material, photographs</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-historical-note field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Historical note:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>John (Jock) Sutherland was born at Elgin, Scotland on 27 January 1877 and was employed from 1891-1894 at Glen Grant Glenlivet Distillery, Rothes, Scotland. He served in South Africa during the South African War (1899-1902) and in 1910 joined the South African Railways where he was employed as a carpenter. Sutherland remained with the S.A.R. until his retirement in 1937, with the exception of military service during World War I. From 1914-1916 he was a corporal in the South African Engineer Corps, serving in German South West Africa. He married Ethel Wynn circa 1922. Jock Sutherland died in Durban circa 1975.</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-digitised field-type-list-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS File list:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Available at KCAL</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-scope-and-content field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Scope and Content:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>The collection comprises one file containing some personal papers and a varied collection of photographs taken in, for example, German South West Africa, Nyasaland and Portuguese East Africa, [1914-1919]</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-shelf field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Shelf:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">SUT</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-provenance field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Provenance:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">-</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-local-system-number field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Local system number:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">KCAL351566</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-taxonomy-vocabulary-6 field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-above clearfix"><h3 class="field-label">Manuscript Inventory: </h3><ul class="links"><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-0"><a href="/?q=taxonomy/term/498" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">Sutherland, John (&#039;Jock&#039;) /Papers</a></li></ul></div>  </div>

      <div class="link-wrapper">
      <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="/?q=node/24446" rel="tag" title="John (Jock) Sutherland papers">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about John (Jock) Sutherland papers</span></a></li>
</ul>    </div>
  
  
