<div id="node-24445" class="node node-content-manuscript-metadata node-promoted node-sticky node-teaser clearfix" about="/?q=node/24445" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">

        <h2>
      <a href="/?q=node/24445">James Stuart papers</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="James Stuart papers" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-field-ms-title field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Title:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">James Stuart papers</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-records field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Date:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">1880s - early 1900s</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-extent field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Extent:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">91 files</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-physical-description field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Physical description:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">manuscripts, typescripts, printed material</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-historical-note field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Historical note:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>James Stuart, 1868-1942, was an official in the Natal Colonial Civil Service and a Zulu linguist.</p>
<p>James Stuart was born in 1868, and joined the Natal Civil Service in the late 1880s.  He served as a magistrate in Natal and Zululand.  He later became Assistant Secretary for Native Affairs in Natal, and, after the Union of South Africa was established, worked for the Union government.  After his retirement, he and his wife moved to England where he died on the 8 March 1942.</p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>See: <em>The Natal Mercury</em>, 19 March 1942.  "Death of Mr. J. Stuart"</p>
<p> </p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-digitised field-type-list-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS File list:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Available at KCAL</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-scope-and-content field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Scope and Content:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>91 files : manuscripts, typescripts, printed material, handwritten notebooks</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-shelf field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Shelf:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">STU</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-provenance field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Provenance:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Original collection</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-local-system-number field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Local system number:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">KCAL291785</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-taxonomy-vocabulary-6 field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-above clearfix"><h3 class="field-label">Manuscript Inventory: </h3><ul class="links"><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-0"><a href="/?q=taxonomy/term/496" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">Stuart, James /Papers</a></li></ul></div>  </div>

      <div class="link-wrapper">
      <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="/?q=node/24445" rel="tag" title="James Stuart papers">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about James Stuart papers</span></a></li>
