<div id="node-24387" class="node node-content-manuscript-metadata node-promoted node-sticky node-teaser clearfix" about="/?q=node/24387" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">

        <h2>
      <a href="/?q=node/24387">Charles R. Sprighton papers</a>
    </h2>
    <span property="dc:title" content="Charles R. Sprighton papers" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-field-ms-title field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Title:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Charles R. Sprighton papers</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-records field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Date:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">1905? - 1993</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-extent field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Extent:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">31 files</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-physical-description field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Physical description:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">manuscripts, typescripts, printed material, newscuttings, photographs</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-historical-note field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Historical note:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>Charles R. Sprighton, Grosvenor</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-digitised field-type-list-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS File list:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Available at KCAL</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-scope-and-content field-type-text-long field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Scope and Content:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>The Charles Sprighton collection comprises 31 files, which include correspondence, reports, legal documents and research notes and documents. Most of the documents in the collection pertain to the "Grosvenor", a British East India merchant ship which sank off the Transkei coast on 4 August 1752 while sailing between Ceylon and England. The collection also reflects Mr Sprighton's interest in early man and evolution, as well as his interest in literature and writing.</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-shelf field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Shelf:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">SPR</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-provenance field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Provenance:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Donation, 2000</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-ms-local-system-number field-type-text field-label-above"><div class="field-label">MS Local system number:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">KCAL350040</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-taxonomy-vocabulary-6 field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-above clearfix"><h3 class="field-label">Manuscript Inventory: </h3><ul class="links"><li class="taxonomy-term-reference-0"><a href="/?q=taxonomy/term/490" typeof="skos:Concept" property="rdfs:label skos:prefLabel" datatype="">Sprighton, Charles R /Papers</a></li></ul></div>  </div>

      <div class="link-wrapper">
      <ul class="links inline"><li class="node-readmore first last"><a href="/?q=node/24387" rel="tag" title="Charles R. Sprighton papers">Read more<span class="element-invisible"> about Charles R. Sprighton papers</span></a></li>
</ul>    </div>
  
  
